entry.title: Russia Exploits Artillery Advantage as Ukraine Braces for Attacks on More Eastern Cities
entry.content: Ukraine issued fresh calls for urgent supplies of weapons from the West, as officials warned that battles in the east increasingly favor Moscow’s better-equipped forces.

entry.title: Effort to Force Russia to Pay Reparations to Ukraine Faces Uphill Battle
entry.content: With the U.S. holding only a fraction of Moscow’s foreign-currency reserves, the options for making Moscow compensate Kyiv for the war are limited.

entry.title: What Do Chinese Consumers Want? Walmart Can't Figure It Out.
entry.content: The hypermarket model is losing ground, local rivals do better on fast delivery, and geopolitics gives the company headaches. Then there’s the red dates problem.
